    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Windshield Wiper Drive Arm Removal</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the windshield wiper arm assembly to be removed and swing the wiper arm out at the
                swivel assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the windshield wiper fluid supply line from the connector at the wiper arm
                base.
            </para>
            <figure id="f47006161" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg47/g47006161.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 161. Windshield Washer Fluid Supply Hose</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. WINDSHIELD WASHER FLUID SUPPLY NIPPLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. WINDSHIELD WIPER ARM FLUID SUPPLY HOSE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the plastic cap assembly covering the wiper arm attachment nut.</para>
            <figure id="f47006162" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg47/g47006162.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 162. Wiper Arm Cap Cover</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. COVER CAP</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. WINDSHIELD WIPER ARM</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. WINDSHIELD WIPER ARM ATTACHMENT NUT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the attachment nut.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make a mark on the wiper arm assembly with a coinciding mark on the wiper drive stud. This
                will help in the re-alignment when re-installing the wiper arm on the drive.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the wiper arm assembly.</para>
            <figure id="f47006163" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg47/g47006163.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 163. Windshield Wiper Arm Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. WINDSHIELD WIPER DRIVE STUD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Follow the same procedure to remove the opposite side wiper drive arm.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
